00:14:56.230 --> 00:14:58.610
And the reason why I said
it's a Japanese knife,

00:14:58.610 --> 00:15:00.990
and it's a Japanese
multi-utility knife.

00:15:00.990 --> 00:15:04.120
You can use it for seafood,
for vegetables, for anything.

00:15:04.120 --> 00:15:06.730
What is different on this
knife, as you can see,

00:15:06.730 --> 00:15:10.700
it has four different
reflections almost.

00:15:10.700 --> 00:15:15.084
Each different reflection is
a different kind of steel.

00:15:15.084 --> 00:15:16.750
So this knife has
four different steels,

00:15:16.750 --> 00:15:18.250
and they are being
pressed together.

00:15:18.250 --> 00:15:20.690
By being pressed together,
they're much stronger,

00:15:20.690 --> 00:15:23.880
and they're not getting as dull
as quickly as regular knives.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.050
And on the top here,
you'll see them-- there's

00:15:26.050 --> 00:15:26.970
very, very small.

00:15:26.970 --> 00:15:27.590
