00:29:24.930 --> 00:29:26.520
The advantage from
fish to seafood

00:29:26.520 --> 00:29:30.280
is you have these
different layers-- flakes.

00:29:30.280 --> 00:29:32.899
And if you're not 100%
when a fish is done,

00:29:32.899 --> 00:29:34.190
you can touch it from the side.

00:29:34.190 --> 00:29:36.721
You don't necessarily want
to touch it from the top.

00:29:36.721 --> 00:29:38.220
In the meat, you
do it from the top.

00:29:38.220 --> 00:29:39.469
And I'll tell you in a second.

00:29:39.469 --> 00:29:42.320
When you touch the seafood
from the side like this

00:29:42.320 --> 00:29:44.760
and the flakes slowly
start to separate--

00:29:44.760 --> 00:29:46.780
you don't want them to
completely fall apart--

00:29:46.780 --> 00:29:48.238
that means your
fish is overcooked.

00:29:48.238 --> 00:29:49.780
Then it's really dead this time.

00:29:49.780 --> 00:29:51.780
But you want to have a
little bit of life in it.

00:29:51.780 --> 00:29:53.140
So you just touch it.

00:29:53.140 --> 00:29:55.900
And as you see, these small
little fish membranes,

00:29:55.900 --> 00:29:57.670
so to speak, are falling apart.

00:29:57.670 --> 00:29:59.040
That's the right temperature.

00:29:59.040 --> 00:30:01.664
Now with a piece of meat,
with a steak or something,

00:30:01.664 --> 00:30:03.580
you touch it from the
top because obviously it

00:30:03.580 --> 00:30:06.640
doesn't have these
flakes to break apart.

00:30:06.640 --> 00:30:07.800
Very simple.

00:30:07.800 --> 00:30:08.399
I'll show you.

00:30:08.399 --> 00:30:10.190
When you hold your hand
like that-- and you

00:30:10.190 --> 00:30:11.620
can all do it with me.

00:30:11.620 --> 00:30:14.740
If you hold your
hand totally relaxed,

00:30:14.740 --> 00:30:17.256
and you press this
part below your thumb,

00:30:17.256 --> 00:30:20.890
that means the cow
is still alive.

00:30:20.890 --> 00:30:22.330
Now basically it's rare.

00:30:22.330 --> 00:30:24.370
That's how the steak is rare.

00:30:24.370 --> 00:30:27.300
So all you need to do now
is no pressure, no nothing.

00:30:27.300 --> 00:30:28.841
Just open your hand.

00:30:28.841 --> 00:30:29.340
Just open.

00:30:29.340 --> 00:30:30.530
No pressure.

00:30:30.530 --> 00:30:32.030
Touch that same area again.

00:30:32.030 --> 00:30:34.180
And you feel a bit of
a difference already.

00:30:34.180 --> 00:30:36.860
Now it's when the
steak is medium rare.

00:30:36.860 --> 00:30:40.060
Now open your hand
as hard as you can.

00:30:40.060 --> 00:30:41.400
Really stretch it.

00:30:41.400 --> 00:30:42.700
And touch it again.

00:30:42.700 --> 00:30:44.950
Now it's medium.

00:30:44.950 --> 00:30:48.910
Now you close your
hand like this

00:30:48.910 --> 00:30:50.660
and put a certain
amount of pressure on it

00:30:50.660 --> 00:30:52.460
so that your
fingernails slightly

00:30:52.460 --> 00:30:55.119
dig into the center
of your hand.

00:30:55.119 --> 00:30:55.910
And press it again.

00:30:55.910 --> 00:30:57.670
You feel the difference now?

00:30:57.670 --> 00:30:59.150
Now it's medium well.

00:30:59.150 --> 00:31:02.180
And now you really make a fist
like you want to hit something.

00:31:02.180 --> 00:31:04.010
Now it's well done.

00:31:04.010 --> 00:31:06.210
Really easy, right?

00:31:06.210 --> 00:31:07.380
So you can do it right here.

00:31:07.380 --> 00:31:08.700
And some other people
they do it here.

00:31:08.700 --> 00:31:09.532
You can do it also.

00:31:09.532 --> 00:31:11.240
But this is the easiest
way for me to do.

00:31:11.240 --> 00:31:13.500
Start from rare all
the way to well done.

00:31:13.500 --> 00:31:14.000
Very easy.

00:31:14.000 --> 00:31:15.100
So this was rare.

00:31:15.100 --> 00:31:15.925
This is well done.

00:31:15.925 --> 00:31:17.050
